=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Esterify 3,5-dihydroxybenzoic acid to methyl 3,5-dihydroxybenzoate (MeOH, catalytic acid), then mono-O-isopropylate with iPrBr/K2CO3 to give methyl 3-hydroxy-5-isopropoxybenzoate (the two phenols are equivalent, so the mono-product is unique). | Step 2: Alkylate the remaining phenol with iBuBr/K2CO3 to obtain methyl 3-isobutoxy-5-isopropoxybenzoate, then hydrolyze the methyl ester (NaOH, H2O/MeOH) to 3-isobutoxy-5-isopropoxybenzoic acid. | Step 3: Convert that acid to the acid chloride (SOCl2), then acylate methyl 2-amino-5-pyridinecarboxylate to form methyl 2-(3-isobutoxy-5-isopropoxybenzamido)-5-pyridinecarboxylate. | Step 4: Saponify the pyridine methyl ester (NaOH, then acid workup) to give the target 2-(3-isobutoxy-5-isopropoxybenzamido)-5-pyridinecarboxylic acid, CC(C)COc1cc(OC(C)C)cc(C(=O)Nc2ccc(C(=O)O)cn2)c1.

